quran[564]{c,v,t}:
  78,1,About what do they ask one another
  78,2,About the great news
  78,3,concerning which they disagree
  78,4,"No, they will come to know"
  78,5,"Again, no, they will come to know"
  78,6,Did We not make the earth habitable
  78,7,and the mountains pegs
  78,8,And We created you in pairs
  78,9,And We made your sleep for rest
  78,10,And We made the night a covering
  78,11,And We made the day (for earning) livelihood
  78,12,And We built above you seven strong ones
  78,13,And We made (the sun) a burning lamp
  78,14,"And We sent down from the rain-clouds, torrential rain"
  78,15,that We may bring forth through it grain and vegetation
  78,16,and dense gardens
  78,17,The day of decision is certainly fixed
  78,18,The day it will be blown into the trumpet (or structure of the universe) you will come forth in groups
  78,19,And the sky will be opened so that it will become gates
  78,20,"and the mountains will be moved away, so that they will become like flowing sand"
  78,21,Hell certainly lies in wait
  78,22,a home for the rebellious
  78,23,They will stay in it for ages
  78,24,They will taste therein neither coolness nor drink
  78,25,"except boiling water and pus*, * Dirty liquid that oozes out of wounds"
  78,26,a reward proportional (to their sins)
  78,27,They certainly did not hope that they would have to account for (their evil deeds)
  78,28,and they denied Our signs with a denial
  78,29,and We have computed everything in a record
  78,30,"So taste (the punishment), and We will not increase for you anything except punishment"
  78,31,For those who guard (against evil there) is certainly an achievement
  78,32,Gardens and vineyards
  78,33,and young women of equal age
  78,34,and a full cup
  78,35,They will hear therein neither useless talk nor falsehood
  78,36,"Reward from your Fosterer, a gift (for the) account (of good deeds)"
  78,37,"The Fosterer of the skies and the earth and that which is between them, the Beneficent, they will not be able to address Him"
  78,38,"The day the spirit (Jibreel) and the angels stand in ranks, they will not speak, except the one who is permitted by the Beneficent and he speaks aright"
  78,39,"That's a real day (not fictitious), so whoever wills let him seek a home near his Fosterer"
  78,40,"We warn you of a punishment that is near, the day man will see that which his hands had sent forth and the infidel will say, “I wish I were dust.”"
  79,1,By those who pull out getting drowned (going deep to the last limit)
  79,2,"and those who untie, releasing"
  79,3,and those who are busy moving swiftly
  79,4,"then those who are ahead, being ahead"
  79,5,then those who manage the affair
  79,6,On the day the quaking one (the earth) will quake
  79,7,and the succeeding one will follow it
  79,8,on that day hearts will palpitate
  79,9,their looks will be cast down
  79,10,"They say, “Shall we be restored to our first state"
  79,11,even when we have become rotten bones?”
  79,12,"They say, “Then this would be a return of loss.”"
  79,13,So it will only be a single shout
  79,14,when they will be awake
  79,15,Has the story of Musa come to you
  79,16,When his Fosterer called him in the holy valley of Tuwa (saying)
  79,17,"Go to Firawn, he has certainly rebelled"
  79,18,"then say to him, “ Have you the inclination to purify yourself"
  79,19,"and that I should guide you to your Fosterer, so that you fear (Him)?”"
  79,20,Then he showed him the great sign
  79,21,but he denied and disobeyed
  79,22,then he turned away in haste
  79,23,then he gathered to proclaim
  79,24,"then said, “I am your top most fosterer.”"
  79,25,So Allah caught him for punishment (both in) the later and the former (life)
  79,26,There is certainly a lesson in that for one who fears
  79,27,Are you the stronger in creation or the sky which He built
  79,28,He raised its height and then set it in equilibrium
  79,29,And He darkened its night and brought out its day light
  79,30,"And He stretched out the earth (drifting the continents apart), after that"
  79,31,brought out from the (earth) its water and its pasture
  79,32,and He firmly anchored the mountains
  79,33,A provision for you and for your cattle
  79,34,So when the great predominating calamity comes
  79,35,the day man will recollect what he earnestly strove after
  79,36,And the hell will be made manifest for him who sees
  79,37,So as for him who rebelled
  79,38,and preferred the life of this world
  79,39,then hell will certainly be his home
  79,40,And as for him who feared to stand before his Fosterer and restrained himself from evil desire
  79,41,then the garden will certainly be his home
  79,42,"They ask you about the hour of doom, “When will be its anchorage (time of happening) ?”"
  79,43,In what way are you to discuss it
  79,44,To your Fosterer (belongs the knowledge of) the ultimate time of its happening
  79,45,You are a warner only for him who fears it
  79,46,"The day they see it, for them it will be as if they had not stayed (in their graves or this world) except for an evening or a morning of it"
  80,1,He (Muhammed) frowned and turned his back
  80,2,that the blind man came to him
  80,3,And what will make you realize that he might have purified himself
  80,4,"or be reminded, so that (your) reminding might have profited him"
  80,5,As for him who is carefree (wealthy)
  80,6,"to him then, you pay attention"
  80,7,"And if he does not purify himself, the responsibility is not on you"
  80,8,And as for him who comes to you striving hard
  80,9,and he fears
  80,10,from him you are distracted
  80,11,"No, it is certainly a reminder"
  80,12,so whoever wills let him remember it
  80,13,(It is) in pages honoured
  80,14,"elevated, clean"
  80,15,in the hands of writers
  80,16,"honoured, virtuous"
  80,17,"Perished be man, how ungrateful he is"
  80,18,From what thing did He create him
  80,19,"He created him from a sperm, then programmed him (to follow a certain path)"
  80,20,"then, He eased that path for him"
  80,21,Then He causes him to die then buries him
  80,22,"Then, when He wills, He will raise him"
  80,23,"No, he has not done that which He commanded him to do"
  80,24,So let man look at his food
  80,25,How We pour water in the form of rain
  80,26,"then We split the earth, (with) a splitting"
  80,27,"then We cause to grow therein, grain"
  80,28,and grapes and green fodder
  80,29,and olive trees and date palms
  80,30,and dense gardens
  80,31,and fruits and herbage
  80,32,A provision for you and for your cattle
  80,33,Then when the deafening sound comes
  80,34,(it will be) a day when man will run away from his brother
  80,35,and his mother and his father
  80,36,and his wife and his sons
  80,37,"on that day, for everyone of them there will be enough concern to keep him unconcerned with others"
  80,38,(Some) faces on that day will be bright
  80,39,"laughing, rejoicing at the good news"
  80,40,(while other) faces on that day will have dust over them
  80,41,being covered with darkness
  80,42,"Those are the infidels, the transgressors"
  81,1,When the sun is made to wind up
  81,2,and when the stars become hazy
  81,3,and when the mountains are moved away
  81,4,and when camels with ten months' pregnancy are left off
  81,5,and when wild animals are brought together
  81,6,and when the oceans are flooded
  81,7,and when the souls are paired (probably with their respective bodies)
  81,8,and when the female child buried alive is asked
  81,9,for what sin she was killed
  81,10,and when the pages are spread
  81,11,and when the sky has its covering removed
  81,12,and when the hell is kindled
  81,13,and when the garden is brought near
  81,14,(every) soul (everyone) will know what (deeds) it has brought for presentation
  81,15,So I do swear by those that withdraw
  81,16,"those that move swiftly, hiding"
  81,17,and the night when it comes (and goes)
  81,18,and the morning when it breathes (and makes us conscious)
  81,19,it is certainly the word of an honoured messenger (Jibreel)
  81,20,"possessor of power, established in the presence (of Allah) to Whom belongs the throne"
  81,21,"one to be obeyed, and with it trustworthy"
  81,22,And your companion (Muhammed) is not possessed by jinn
  81,23,And he (Muhammed) saw him (Jibreel) on the clear horizon
  81,24,And he is not a miser concealing (information) of the unseen
  81,25,And it is not the word of the cursed devil
  81,26,So in' which direction are you all going
  81,27,The (Quran) is nothing but a reminder to the worlds
  81,28,for him among you who wills to be upright
  81,29,"And you do not will unless Allah, the Fosterer of the worlds, wills"
  82,1,When the sky is cleft asunder
  82,2,and when the planets are made to fall
  82,3,and when the oceans are made to overflow
  82,4,and when the graves are overturned
  82,5,(every) soul will know what it had advanced (preferred) and what it had kept behind (not preferred)
  82,6,O man ! what has deceived you concerning your Honoured Fosterer
  82,7,"Who created you, then set the equilibrium in you so as to balance you"
  82,8,"In whatever form He willed, He constituted you"
  82,9,"No, but you deny the (day of) judgment"
  82,10,And certainly over you are custodians
  82,11,honoured recorders
  82,12,they know what you do
  82,13,The righteous will certainly be in bliss
  82,14,And the transgressors will certainly be in hell
  82,15,They will enter it on the day of judgment
  82,16,and they will not be absent from it
  82,17,And what will make you realize what the day of judgment is
  82,18,"Again, what will make you realize what the day of judgment is"
  82,19,"The day on which no soul (person) will have any power on another soul (person), and the command on that day will be (totally) Allah’s"
  83,1,Sorrowful is the state of those who measure and weigh less than what is due
  83,2,"those who, when they take by measure from other people, they take in full"
  83,3,"but when they measure or weigh for others, they make it less than what is due"
  83,4,Do they not expect that they will be raised (after their death)
  83,5,for a great day
  83,6,the day mankind will stand before the Fosterer of the worlds
  83,7,"No, certainly the record of (deeds) of the transgressors will be in Sijjin"
  83,8,And what will make you realize what Sijjin is
  83,9,(It is a) written record
  83,10,"Sorrowful will be the state on that day, of the deniers"
  83,11,who deny the day of judgment
  83,12,"And no one denies it except every exceeder of limits, a sinner"
  83,13,"When Our signs are read to him, he says, “Ancient stories.”"
  83,14,"No, but that which they have earned is rust on their hearts"
  83,15,"No, on that day they will certainly be curtained from their Fosterer"
  83,16,then they will certainly enter the hell
  83,17,"then it will be said, “This is that which you made a denial of.”"
  83,18,"No, certainly the record of (deeds of) the righteous will be in Illiyin"
  83,19,and what will make you realize what Illiyun is
  83,20,(It is a) written record
  83,21,Those who are brought near will witness it
  83,22,The righteous will certainly be in bliss
  83,23,They will be seeing (reclining) on couches
  83,24,"You will recognize in their faces, radiance of bliss"
  83,25,"They will be given to drink from a pure drink, sealed"
  83,26,"The seal of which is of musk. So let those who wish to put in conscious effort, put in a conscious effort for that"
  83,27,And it is admixed with Tasniim
  83,28,a spring from which those who are brought near will drink
  83,29,The criminals certainly used to laugh at those who believed
  83,30,and when they passed by them they used to wink at one another
  83,31,"And when they returned to their class of people, they returned joyful in false pride"
  83,32,"And when they saw them they said, “These are certainly the persons who are astray,”"
  83,33,though they were not sent as custodians over them
  83,34,"So this day, those who had believed will laugh at the infidels"
  83,35,They will be seeing (reclining) on couches
  83,36,Will not the infidels be rewarded according to what they used to do
  84,1,When the sky is split asunder
  84,2,"and responds to its Fosterer, a duty incumbent on it"
  84,3,And when the earth is stretched out
  84,4,and casts forth that which is in it and becomes empty
  84,5,"and responds to its Fosterer, a duty incumbent on it"
  84,6,"O man! you are certainly labouring towards your Fosterer, with a labour, so you will meet Him"
  84,7,So as for him who is given his record (of deeds) in his right hand
  84,8,"he will be called to account, with an easy accountability"
  84,9,and he will return happily to his class of people
  84,10,And as for him who is given his record (of deeds) behind his back
  84,11,he will call for (i.e. invoke) destruction (upon himself)
  84,12,and he will enter the (hot) blaze
  84,13,He was certainly happy in his class of people (in the worldly life)
  84,14,He certainly thought that he would never return
  84,15,"Why not, his Fosterer was certainly seeing him"
  84,16,So I do swear by the redness of the sunset
  84,17,and the night and that which it gathers
  84,18,and the moon when it is full
  84,19,You will definitely be carried from stage to stage
  84,20,So what is wrong with them that they do not believe
  84,21,"And when the Quran is, recited to them, they do not prostrate"
  84,22,"No, those who do not believe, deny"
  84,23,And Allah knows best what they hide
  84,24,So give them the news of the painful punishment
  84,25,"except those who believe and do righteous works, for them there is an unfailing reward"
  85,1,By the sky containing galaxies of stars
  85,2,and the promised day
  85,3,and the witness and the witnessed
  85,4,Be killed owners of the pit
  85,5,(of) the fire containing fuel
  85,6,when they sat around it
  85,7,And they were (themselves) witnesses over that which they did with the believers
  85,8,"And they did not avenge them except (for the fact) that they believed in Allah, the Mighty, the Praised"
  85,9,"Whose is the kingdom of the skies and the earth, and Allah is a Witness over everything"
  85,10,"Those who persecute the believing men and the believing women then do not repent, then certainly for them is the punishment of hell and for them is the punishment of burning"
  85,11,"Those who believe and do righteous works, certainly, for them are the gardens beneath which rivers flow. That is the great achievement"
  85,12,The grip of your Fosterer is certainly strong
  85,13,It is certainly He Who causes to begin (originates) and causes to repeat (reproduces)
  85,14,"And He is Protectively Forgiving, the Loving"
  85,15,Possessor of the glorious throne
  85,16,Doer of what He intends
  85,17,Has there come to you the story of the armies of
  85,18,Firawn and Samood
  85,19,"No, those who do not believe are in falsehood"
  85,20,and Allah encompasses them from every side (without their notice)
  85,21,"No, it is a glorious Quran"
  85,22,in a guarded tablet
  86,1,By the sky and the Taariq
  86,2,And what will make you realize what Taariq is
  86,3,(It is) the piercing star
  86,4,There is not a single soul which does not have a custodian over it
  86,5,So let man see from what he was created
  86,6,He was created from gushing water (fluid)
  86,7,that comes out from in between the loins and the ribs
  86,8,"He is certainly able to return him, (and make him face)"
  86,9,"the day, (when) secrets will be examined"
  86,10,then there will neither be strength nor a helper for him
  86,11,By the sky that returns (the water in the form of rain)
  86,12,and the earth that splits (due to vegetation)
  86,13,this (Quran) is certainly a decisive statement
  86,14,and it is not (something to be taken as) a joke
  86,15,They certainly plot a plot
  86,16,and I (too) plot a plot
  86,17,"So give time to the infidels, give them time for a while"
  87,1,"Glorify the name of your Fosterer, the Most High"
  87,2,Who created then set the equilibrium
  87,3,and Who programmed then guided (to the programme)
  87,4,And Who brought forth the pasture
  87,5,then made it dust coloured rubbish
  87,6,"We will make you recite, so that you will not forget"
  87,7,"except that which Allah wills, He certainly knows the manifest and (also) that which is hidden"
  87,8,And We will make your (way) easy for the easy (way)
  87,9,"So remind, if reminding is profitable"
  87,10,he who fears will be reminded
  87,11,and he who is unfortunate will turn away from it
  87,12,he who will enter the great fire
  87,13,then he will neither die therein nor live
  87,14,He succeeds who purifies himself
  87,15,"and remembers the name of his Fosterer, then worships (offers salat)"
  87,16,"No, you prefer the life of this world"
  87,17,while the hereafter is better and that which remains
  87,18,This is certainly there in the earlier books (too)
  87,19,books of lbrahim and Musa
  88,1,Have the details of the happenings on the (day of the final) covering come to you
  88,2,Faces on that day will be downcast
  88,3,"labouring, weary"
  88,4,entering very hot fire
  88,5,being made to drink from boiling spring
  88,6,There will be no food for them except that from the thorn tree
  88,7,It will neither be nourishable by them nor will it make them free from hunger
  88,8,(Other) faces that day will be happy
  88,9,pleased on account of the effort they had put in earlier
  88,10,(They will be) in a high garden
  88,11,therein you will not hear useless talk
  88,12,therein is a flowing spring
  88,13,therein are raised couches
  88,14,and drinking cups placed ready (for use)
  88,15,and cushions set in rows
  88,16,and carpets spread
  88,17,So do they not see towards the camel how it is created
  88,18,and towards the sky how it is raised
  88,19,and towards the mountains how they are rooted
  88,20,and towards the earth how it is spread
  88,21,"So remind, you are only to remind"
  88,22,You are not in authority over them
  88,23,But one who turns away and does not believe
  88,24,so he will be punished by Allah with a great punishment
  88,25,Their return is certainly towards Us
  88,26,"then certainly, it is on Us to take their account"
  89,1,By the dawn
  89,2,and the ten nights
  89,3,and the even and the odd
  89,4,and the night when it travels
  89,5,"For one who has sense, these (items) are surely worth being sworn by"
  89,6,Did you not see how your Fosterer dealt with Aad
  89,7,"people of Iram, possessors of (lofty buildings supported by) pillars"
  89,8,the like of which was not created in (other) cities
  89,9,and Samood who cut the rocks in the valley
  89,10,"and Firawn, possessor of pegs"
  89,11,who rebelled in the cities
  89,12,Thus they increased corruption in them
  89,13,So your Fosterer poured on them a portion of the punishment
  89,14,Your Fosterer is certainly watchfully waiting
  89,15,"So as for man, whenever his Fosterer tries him by honouring him and favouring him, then he says, “My Fosterer has honoured me.”"
  89,16,"And as for (the situation) when He tries him by straitening on him his provision, he says, “My Fosterer has disgraced me.”"
  89,17,"No, but the orphan is not honoured by you"
  89,18,and you do not urge one another on the feeding of the poor
  89,19,"and you eat off the inheritance, eating it greedily"
  89,20,and you love wealth with intense love
  89,21,"No, when the earth is crushed to level it in a level"
  89,22,and your Fosterer comes with the angels in rank after rank
  89,23,"so on that day, hell will be brought near, (and) on that day man will be mindful. But his being mindful (on that day) will be of no use to him"
  89,24,"He will say, \"I wish I had sent (good deeds) before, for my life (after death)"
  89,25,"So on that day, no one’s punishment will be like His punishment"
  89,26,and no one's binding will be like His binding
  89,27,O you peaceful soul
  89,28,Return to your Fosterer pleased and pleasing (Him)
  89,29,so enter among My servants
  89,30,and enter My garden
  90,1,"No, I do swear by this city (Mecca)"
  90,2,and you are a dweller of this city
  90,3,and by the begetter (father) and that which he begot (son)
  90,4,We have indeed created man in hardship
  90,5,Does he think that no one will ever have power over him
  90,6,"He says, “I have destroyed plenty of wealth.”"
  90,7,Does he think that no one sees him
  90,8,Did We not make for him two eyes
  90,9,and a tongue and two lips
  90,10,and show him the two high ways (of good and evil)
  90,11,But he did not attempt the uphill (road)
  90,12,And what will make you realize what the uphill (road) is
  90,13,Freeing a slave
  90,14,or feeding during a period of hunger
  90,15,an orphan having relationship
  90,16,or the dusty poor
  90,17,then to be among those who believe and recommend to each other patience and recommend to each other compassion
  90,18,Those are the companions of the right hand (side)
  90,19,"And those who do not believe in Our signs, they are the companions of the left hand (side)"
  90,20,Fire will be closed over them (enveloping them from all sides)
  91,1,By the sun and its light
  91,2,and the moon when it reflects it
  91,3,and the day when it unveils it
  91,4,and the night when it covers it
  91,5,and the sky and Him Who built it
  91,6,and the earth and Him Who spread it
  91,7,and the soul and Him Who balanced it
  91,8,"then inspired in it, its transgressions and its guarding (against evils)"
  91,9,He indeed succeeds who purifies it
  91,10,and he indeed fails who buries it
  91,11,Samood denied (the truth) due to their rebellion
  91,12,when the most wretched of them broke forth
  91,13,"The messenger of Allah told them, “It is the she-camel of Allah, so let her drink.”"
  91,14,But they denied him and slaughtered her so their Fosterer destroyed them due to their sin and thus balanced it (the destruction was equal to their crime)
  91,15,And He does not fear its consequence
  92,1,By the night when it covers (the sun)
  92,2,and the day when it unveils (the sun)
  92,3,and Him Who created the male and the female
  92,4,Your striving is certainly for diverse ends
  92,5,So as for him who gave and guarded (against evil)
  92,6,and accepted that which was best
  92,7,We will facilitate him for ease
  92,8,And as for him who was niggardly and considered himself independent
  92,9,and denied that which was best
  92,10,We will facilitate him for difficulty
  92,11,And his wealth will not keep him safe from difficulty when he perishes
  92,12,It is certainly on Us to guide
  92,13,"And certainly, Ours is the latter (future) and the former (past)"
  92,14,So I warn you of the blazing fire
  92,15,None will enter it except the wretched
  92,16,who denied and turned away
  92,17,And one who guards (against evil) will be saved from it
  92,18,he who gives his wealth for his self purification
  92,19,"and he does not bestow favour on anyone, from that which is with him, (with the intention of) being rewarded (back)"
  92,20,"but he seeks the Attention of his Fosterer, the High"
  92,21,And he will surely be pleased
  93,1,By the brightness of the day
  93,2,and the night when it darkens
  93,3,Your Fosterer has neither forsaken you nor does he hate you
  93,4,And surely the latter period (future) will be better for you than the former (past)
  93,5,And surely you will be given (so much) by your Fosterer that you will be pleased
  93,6,"Did He not find you an orphan, then give you shelter"
  93,7,and find you wandering then guide you
  93,8,and find you poor then make you free of want
  93,9,So as for the orphan do not oppress (him)
  93,10,and as for the beggar do not drive him away
  93,11,"and as for the favour of your Fosterer, do proclaim"
  94,1,Did We not expand for you your bosom
  94,2,and relieve you of your burden
  94,3,which weighed down your back
  94,4,and exalted for you your mention
  94,5,So certainly with difficulty is ease
  94,6,Certainly with difficulty is ease
  94,7,"So when you are free, then strive"
  94,8,and turn your attention towards your Fosterer
  95,1,"By the fig (or the place Tiin where Nuh’s ship embarked), and the olive (or Zaita in Jerusalam, were Isa-ibni-Maryam received and preached the message of Allah)"
  95,2,and Mount Sinai (where Musa received the message of Allah)
  95,3,"and this city of security (Mecca, where our prophet Muhammed initially received and preached the message of Allah, all these are witnesses that)"
  95,4,We had indeed created man in the best form
  95,5,then We brought him back as the lowest of those who are low
  95,6,"except those who believed and did righteous works, then for them there is an unfailing reward"
  95,7,Then after this what makes you deny the judgment
  95,8,"Is not Allah the Best Judge, of all the judges"
  96,1,Recite in the name of your Fosterer Who created
  96,2,He created man from something that clings and hangs (like a leech)
  96,3,"Recite, and your Fosterer is the Most Honourable"
  96,4,Who taught with the pen
  96,5,He taught man that which he did not know
  96,6,"No, man certainly rebels"
  96,7,because he sees himself independent
  96,8,"Certainly, towards your Fosterer is the return"
  96,9,Have you seen him who forbids
  96,10,when a servant of Allah worships
  96,11,"Have you seen, if he is on guidance"
  96,12,or enjoins guarding (against evil)
  96,13,"Have you seen, if he denies and turns (his back)"
  96,14,did he not know that Allah certainly sees
  96,15,"No, if he does not stop, We will drag him, seizing him by his forelock"
  96,16,"the denying, sinful forelock"
  96,17,So let him call his council
  96,18,We will call the soldiers (guards of hell)
  96,19,"No, do not obey him but prostrate and draw near (to Allah)"
  97,1,We certainly sent it** down during the night of Al Qadr. ** The Quran
  97,2,And what will make you realize what the night of Al Qadr is
  97,3,The night of Al Qadr is better than a thousand months
  97,4,The angels and the spirit come down during this night by the permission of their Fosterer with (a programme for) every affair
  97,5,Peace! it is till the appearance of dawn
  98,1,Those who do not believe from among the owners of the book and the polytheists would not have left off (falsehood) till the clear proof had come to them (in the form of)
  98,2,"a messenger from Allah, reading clean pages"
  98,3,containing established ordinances
  98,4,And those who were given the book did not become divided except after the clear proof came to them
  98,5,"And they were not ordered anything except that they should serve Allah, keeping religion exclusively for Him, being those who stand firm on that which is right, and (that they should) establish worship (salat) and give charity (zakat), and that is the established religion"
  98,6,"Those who do not believe from among the owners of the book and the polytheists will certainly be in the fire of hell, staying therein, those are the persons who are the worst of creatures"
  98,7,Those who believe and do righteous works those certainly are the persons who are the best of creatures
  98,8,"Their reward is with their Fosterer: Gardens of everlasting bliss, underneath which rivers flow, they will stay therein for ever, Allah pleased with them and they pleased with Him. That is for him who fears his Fosterer"
  99,1,When the earth is quaked with its quaking
  99,2,and the earth brings out its weighty material
  99,3,"and man will say, “What ails her ?”"
  99,4,She will be made to tell her news on that day
  99,5,because your Fosterer (would have) communicated to her
  99,6,"On that day human beings will be brought forth in diverse groups, to be shown their deeds"
  99,7,"So whoever does good equivalent in weight, even to a small particle, will see it"
  99,8,"And whoever does evil equivalent in weight, even to a small particle, will see it"
  100,1,By those that move fast breathing heavily
  100,2,then those that strike fire striking
  100,3,then those that raid at dawn
  100,4,then thereby raise dust
  100,5,then penetrate into the midst of an assembly
  100,6,Man is certainly ungrateful to his Fosterer
  100,7,and he himself is a witness over that
  100,8,And he certainly has intense love for good (worldly wealth)
  100,9,"Then does he not know, that when that which is in the graves is exposed"
  100,10,and that which is in the bosoms is made to appear (i.e. secrets are revealed)
  100,11,"certainly on that day, their Fosterer is fully informed about them"
  101,1,The calamity
  101,2,What is the calamity
  101,3,And what will make you realize what the calamity is? (It will befall on)
  101,4,the day when mankind will be like scattered moths
  101,5,and the mountains will be like loosened wool
  101,6,Then as for him whose weights (of good deeds) are heavy
  101,7,then he will lead a life of pleasure
  101,8,And as for him whose weights (of good deeds) are light
  101,9,then his home* will be in a deep pit (of hell). * Destination
  101,10,And what will make you realize what the (deep pit of hell) is
  101,11,(It is a) very hot fire
  102,1,Rivalry in worldly increase distracts you (from the remembrance of Allah)
  102,2,till you come to the graves
  102,3,"No, you will know"
  102,4,"Again, no, you will know"
  102,5,"No, if you know (having) the knowledge that is certain"
  102,6,you will definitely see hell fire
  102,7,Then you will definitely see it with the eye of certainty
  102,8,Then on that day you will definitely be questioned about the comforts
  103,1,By the time (i.e. historic time is witness that)
  103,2,Man is certainly at a loss
  103,3,"except those who believe and do righteous works and recommend to one another, the truth, and recommend to one another, patience"
  104,1,"Sorrowful is the state of every slanderer, defamer"
  104,2,who accumulates wealth and keeps on counting it
  104,3,He thinks that his wealth will make him immortal
  104,4,"No, he will definitely be flung into the crushing one"
  104,5,And what will make you realize what the crushing one is
  104,6,"(It is the) fire of Allah, kindled"
  104,7,which is made to rise over the hearts
  104,8,it will certainly be closed on them
  104,9,in columns that are stretched
  105,1,"Did you not consider, how your Fosterer dealt with the owners of the elephant"
  105,2,Did He not make their plot useless
  105,3,and send on them flocks of flying creatures
  105,4,who pelted them with stones of baked clay
  105,5,so that He made them like eaten up straw (husk)
  106,1,For the taming of Quraysh
  106,2,their taming in equipping caravans (for traveling) in winter and summer
  106,3,so let them serve the Fosterer of this house (Kaaba)
  106,4,Who has fed them in hunger and given them security from fear
  107,1,Did you see him who belies religion
  107,2,Then he is the one who pushes away the orphan
  107,3,and does not urge on the feeding of the poor
  107,4,So sorrowful is the state of the worshippers
  107,5,who are heedless of their worship (salat)
  107,6,(in the sense that they are) those who make a show (of their worship)
  107,7,and refuse small kindness
  108,1,We certainly gave you abundance
  108,2,so worship your Fosterer and sacrifice
  108,3,"The one who hates you, he is certainly without posterity"
  109,1,"Say, “O Infidels"
  109,2,I do not serve (worship) that which you serve (worship)
  109,3,And you are not servers of that which I serve
  109,4,And I am not a server of that which you serve
  109,5,And you are not servers of that which I serve
  109,6,For you your religion (or judgment) and for me my religion (or judgment).”
  110,1,When Allah's help and the victory comes
  110,2,and you see people enter the religion of Allah in troops
  110,3,then glorify your Fosterer by praising Him and seek His protective forgiveness. He is certainly the Accepter of repentance
  111,1,May the hands of Abu Lahab perish. And may he perish
  111,2,His wealth and that which he earned will not save him
  111,3,He will enter flaming fire
  111,4,and his wife (too who is a) carrier of fire-wood
  111,5,In her neck (there will be) a rope of palm-fibre
  112,1,"Say, “Allah is One"
  112,2,Allah is He on Whom all depend
  112,3,He does not beget and He is not begotten
  112,4,And there is no one equal to Him.”
  113,1,"Say, “I seek the protection of the Fosterer of the day break"
  113,2,from the evil of that which He has created
  113,3,and from the evil of the darkness (of night) when it overspreads
  113,4,and from the evil of women blowing in the knots (practicing witchcraft)
  113,5,and from the evil of the envier when he envies.”
  114,1,"Say, “I seek the protection of the Fosterer of mankind"
  114,2,the King of mankind
  114,3,the God of mankind
  114,4,"from the evil of the whisperings of (the devil), he who (whispers and then) withdraws"
  114,5,who whispers into the bosoms (hearts or minds) of mankind
  114,6,from among the jinn and mankind.”